In his weekly address, President Trump discusses his recent foreign trip, highlighting his visits to Saudi Arabia, Israel, Italy, and the Vatican. He emphasizes his goal of advancing American interests, building coalitions against terrorism, and promoting peace, prosperity, and hope. He mentions the summit with Muslim and Arab nations, the opening of a center to combat extremist ideology, and an economic development deal. He also mentions his meetings with Palestinian leader President Abbas and Pope Francis. He concludes by expressing his gratitude for American military families and touting the achievements of his trip in paving the way for cooperation and peace.